“And how we burned in the camps later, thinking: What would things have been like if every Security operative, when he went out at night to make an arrest, had been uncertain whether he would return alive and had to say good-bye to his family? The Organs would very quickly have suffered a shortage of officers and transport and, notwithstanding all of Stalin's thirst, the cursed machine would have ground to a halt! Japan recently implemented ID to Apple Wallet nationwide. I understand that this is something the US struggles with as it consists of a federal government. The Japanese Digital Agency also released a verifier app that anyone can use without paying or paperwork. Japan does not need ID to ride airplanes; however, it is now legally accepted as a formal type of ID just like the physical one: to print out certificates, authorize medical privileges in hospitals, banks, and phone sellers, yet drive without a physical license is still on the way. Foreign tourists will be able to make age verifications at convenience stores just like residents in Japan. Interoperability across countries is key, and I wish the US would take this leadership!
